 the total contribution is the sum of each individual contribution:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathring{R}_{1}=\mathring{Y}_{1}=\sum_{i}^{I}\left[S_{i}\sum_{N=1}^{\infty}p_{i,N}\cdot C_{N}^{1}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathring{R}_{2}=\sum_{i}^{I}\left[S_{i}\sum_{N=2}^{\infty}p_{i,N}\cdot C_{N}^{2}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathring{Y}_{2}(\tau)=\frac{\mathring{R}_{2,i}}{\tau}\,\intop_{0}^{\tau}dt\cdot cdf_{i}(t)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With the subscript 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 denoting the contribution of the source of type 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 among 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 sources.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathring{Y}(\tau)$
\end_inset

 is still calculated through two times the ratio of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathring{Y}_{2}$
\end_inset

